problem:
A teacher opens a can of food in the front of a classroom. Soon, all of the students in the classroom can smell the food. Which statement identifies a property of a gas that allows all of the students to smell the food?
Choices:
  A: A gas has no mass.
  B: A gas has a large mass.
  C: A gas takes the shape of its container.
  D: A gas keeps its shape when placed in a container.
choices:
Choices:
  A: A gas has no mass.
  B: A gas has a large mass.
  C: A gas takes the shape of its container.
  D: A gas keeps its shape when placed in a container.
response:
Thought: 
The smell of the food is able to spread throughout the classroom because gases can diffuse. Diffusion is the movement of particles from an area of high concentration to an area of low concentration. This is possible because gas particles are constantly moving and colliding with each other.
Action: Answer("C")

response:
